cs.SC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with algorithms for computing the Hermite form of a matrix of differential polynomials, which is a problem in symbolic computation. This makes cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves polynomial operations, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions unimodular matrices, which are commonly used in linear algebra, making cs.LO (Linear Algebra) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the time complexity of the algorithm, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
